---
// Ported from _src/content/notes/body.html via scripts/port-page.mjs.
// SEO mirrors tests/seo-fixture.json. JSON-LD lands in Phase 8.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Notes on Personal Systems, Learning &amp;amp; Better Thinking | Jevan Goldsmith"
  description="A working notebook of Jevan Goldsmith's ideas on personal systems, learning, decisions, and useful experiments."
  canonical="https://jevangoldsmith.com/notes.html"
>
<main class="notes-content">
        <header class="notes-header">
            <p class="section-eyebrow">Thinking in Public</p>
            <h1 class="notes-title">Notes</h1>
            <p class="notes-intro">Quick thoughts, book takeaways, and ideas I'm still figuring out. Less polished than essays, more honest about what I don't know yet.</p>
        </header>
        <div class="categories-filter">
            <span class="category-tag active">All</span>
            <span class="category-tag">Books</span>
            <span class="category-tag">Business</span>
            <span class="category-tag">Life</span>
            <span class="category-tag">Tech</span>
        </div>
        <div class="featured-note">
            <div class="featured-note-header">
                <span class="featured-badge">Pinned</span>
                <span class="note-date">Jan 2026</span>
            </div>
            <h3>Why I Started Writing Notes in Public</h3>
            <p>Most of what I think about never makes it into a polished essay. These notes are my attempt to share the messy middle - the half-formed ideas, the questions I'm wrestling with, and the things I'm reading that are shaping how I think.</p>
            <a href="#" class="featured-note-link">Read more →</a>
        </div>
        <section class="notes-section">
            <p class="section-eyebrow">Recent Notes</p>
            <h2 class="section-title">What I've Been Thinking About</h2>
            <div class="notes-grid">
                <a href="#" class="note-card"><div class="note-meta"><span class="note-category">Books</span><span class="note-date">Jan 28, 2026</span></div><h3 class="note-title">Notes on "The Almanack of Naval Ravikant"</h3><p class="note-excerpt">Specific knowledge is found by pursuing your genuine curiosity rather than whatever is hot right now...</p></a>
                <a href="#" class="note-card"><div class="note-meta"><span class="note-category">Business</span><span class="note-date">Jan 22, 2026</span></div><h3 class="note-title">The Problem with "Best Practices"</h3><p class="note-excerpt">Best practices are average practices. They're what everyone does, which means they can't be a source of competitive advantage...</p></a>
                <a href="#" class="note-card"><div class="note-meta"><span class="note-category">Life</span><span class="note-date">Jan 15, 2026</span></div><h3 class="note-title">On Saying No More Often</h3><p class="note-excerpt">Every yes is a no to something else. I've been tracking what I say yes to this month and realizing how often I'm trading what matters for what's urgent...</p></a>
                <a href="#" class="note-card"><div class="note-meta"><span class="note-category">Tech</span><span class="note-date">Jan 8, 2026</span></div><h3 class="note-title">Building in Public vs Building in Private</h3><p class="note-excerpt">There's a tension between sharing your work early for feedback and protecting ideas until they're ready...</p></a>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="recent-notes-section">
            <p class="section-eyebrow">Archive</p>
            <h2 class="section-title">All Notes</h2>
            <div class="notes-list">
                <a href="#" class="note-list-item"><div class="note-list-content"><span class="note-category">Books</span><span class="note-list-title">Lessons from "Zero to One"</span></div><span class="note-list-date">Dec 2025</span></a>
                <a href="#" class="note-list-item"><div class="note-list-content"><span class="note-category">Life</span><span class="note-list-title">The compound effect of small decisions</span></div><span class="note-list-date">Dec 2025</span></a>
                <a href="#" class="note-list-item"><div class="note-list-content"><span class="note-category">Business</span><span class="note-list-title">Why culture eats strategy</span></div><span class="note-list-date">Nov 2025</span></a>
                <a href="#" class="note-list-item"><div class="note-list-content"><span class="note-category">Tech</span><span class="note-list-title">Tools I'm using right now</span></div><span class="note-list-date">Nov 2025</span></a>
            </div>
        </section>
</main>
</Base>
